# 4. 寄り添うように

Len: ♪————! ♪————!
Len: ♪————! ♪————!!
Len: That doesn't sound right...
Len: (Miku sounded way better than this during the girls' show.)
Len: (They launched everyone sky high just through their singing.)
Len: (Which means I gotta figure out a way to sing like Miku did that time...!)
Miku: Len, how's it going?
Len: Oh, Miku...!
Len: I'm playing my guitar just fine, but I'm not as happy with my singing.
Miku: Your singing?
Len: Yeah...
Len: Um, Miku? What did you feel as you sang during the girls' show...?
Miku: What did I feel...?
Miku: Well, I was definitely having fun. It felt wonderful knowing that my singing was helping bring everybody together.
Miku: Not much other than that to be honest.
Len: Wait, really?
Miku: Yes, really.
Miku: Also, well... When I was singing, I...
Miku: I tried to tell the girls that they can play even better. That they can keep going.
Miku: In that sense, I sang with the hope to propel them forward.
Len: The hope to propel them forward...
Miku: Yes. I realized something after spending so much time with them...
Miku: We may not be able to do much for them directly, but we can think about things and try to come up with good solutions together...
Miku: Singing is the same. You can't solve people's problems directly with it, but you can move them or show support.
Miku: Which is why... I wanted to sing in a way that would help Ichika and the others achieve that goal.
Miku: I wanted to help the girls move forward even just a little bit.
Len: I see...
Len: Yeah, I think I have a much better idea of what I need to do now.
Len: Thanks, Miku!
Miku: You're welcome, and good luck. I'll be heading back to practice now.
Len: Okay! See you in a bit!
Len: Propel them forward...
Len: Okay.
Len: Wait, huh...? There's something shining by that chair...
Len: Did Rin drop it? Saki did just get her some new accessories.
Len: I guess I should pick it up for her and...
Len: Huh...?!
Rin: ♪————...
Rin: (Kanade's song really does have this warmth to it...)
Rin: (It's like it knows how to meld with your heart and comfort you in just the right way...)
Rin: (When Miku sang that time, she must've done so to try to convey Kanade's feelings and comfort Mafuyu.)
Rin: I wanna learn how to sing like that...
Rin: ♪————...
MEIKO: ...
???: MEIKO.
MEIKO: ...!
MEIKO: What's the matter...?
Miku: Mizuki and Ena bought some snacks for us.
Len: A-And we were looking for Rin...
MEIKO: Rin wants to focus on what she's doing right now, so you shouldn't disturb her...
Miku: We shouldn't?
Len: Is something bothering her...? Are you sure she doesn't need our help...?
MEIKO: Nothing's bothering her. It's just... I'm sure she'll come see you when she feels she's ready.
Len: Okay...
Miku: We understand... For now, let's go join the others.
Miku: We'll set aside some of these for Rin.
MEIKO: Yes, let's do that.
Len: S-So, um... MEIKO, you're welcome to join us. We'll be just over there.
Rin: ♪———— ♪————...
MEIKO: (I can't do what Rin's doing right now...)
MEIKO: Still, I...
MEIKO: ♪————...
MEIKO: ...? This light...
Rin: Huh? What...?
MEIKO & Rin: ...!
